en_179898_0	Presidential Commission of Inquiry to Inquire and Investigate into Serious Acts of Fraud and Corruption will hand over reports of nearly 15 cases of serious fraud and corruption to President Maithripala Sirisena today (Jan. 02).
en_179898_1	The Commission, in addition to the reports of the 15 cases of serious fraud and corruption prepared after extensive investigations and analysis of evidence, will also hand over the recommendations on the measures to be taken in future to prevent such crimes.
en_179898_2	Meanwhile, President Maithripala Sirisena will make a special statement tomorrow on the final report of the Presidential Commission of Inquiry into the Bond Issuance of the Central Bank of Sri Lanka.
en_179898_3	The final report of the Commission was handed over to the President on 30th of December 2017.
en_179898_4	The three-member Commission was headed by the Supreme Court Judge K.T Chithrasiri.
en_179898_5	Meanwhile, the JVP says that they hope to make a request to the President’s Secretary on obtaining a copy of the report handed over by the presidential commission that investigated the bond issue.
en_179898_6	The JVP Politburo member, Wasantha Samarasinghe noted that the necessary request form will be submitted to the President’s Secretary this morning.
